{
  "stem": "17308.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 102.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In the Vichy area, they had, already, to follow some German instructions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one of these instructions, that military men could not leave the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, I managed to get a visa for somewhere just to go-- a courtesy visa what was Central America [INAUDIBLE], at the time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But when I wanted to cross the border, they wouldn't allow me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at the first stage I wasn't so worried about this, because you used to take information-- information were good.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The authorities gave you information saying there's nothing to worry-- behavior of the German is good.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was nothing anti-Jewish said at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I wasn't worried.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had a guilt feeling later-- must be honest-- a guilt feeling from a certain letter that I got from my parents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they seemed to blame me that I couldn't tell them what to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, this was, rather, stage where things were bad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I couldn't tell them-- well, even if I would have told them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "First, mail was censored.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You can't write what you want in the mail.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and, well, I really thought they should have left Belgium, but I couldn't write so-- And it wasn't easy to leave at the time already.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Control was severe.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in fact, some of my family from the States tried to get them out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They booked them, even, a passage from Lisbon on a Portuguese boat to go to the States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They made all the arrangements, but unfortunately they couldn't leave.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Officially, they couldn't leave unless they managed to smuggle out of the-- I suppose they couldn't find a way for doing it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Some people managed, some didn't manage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Very few managed to leave the country at that time, because everything was controlled, checked by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
